The paper deals with fine-grained image recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning implicit part representations and using a region attention mechanism, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve evaluating the performance on three different datasets, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
